{"lemma": "ثالِثٌ", "slug": "ثالِثٌ", "root": "ث.ل.ث", "root_slug": "ث-ل-ث", "root_link": "/words/roots/ث-ل-ث", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "ثالِث", "root": "ثلث", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 2}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["adj"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n4638"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D8%AB%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "third", "fa": "سوم", "ur": "تیسرا", "tr": "üçüncü", "id": "ketiga", "bn": "তৃতীয়", "es": "tercero", "fr": "troisième", "de": "dritter", "ru": "третий", "zh": "第三"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "third"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/θaː.liθ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n4638", "headword_ar": "ثَالِثٌ", "root": "vlv", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Third"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: fem. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T, &c.) The final"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "v", "text_ar": "ث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alv~aAlivu", "text_ar": "الثَّالِثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is sometimes changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa vaAlivu valaAvapK", "text_ar": "هُوَ ثَالِثُ ثَلَاثَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, is the third of three"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: thus you say when the two [terms] agree, each with the other; but not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vaAlivN valaAvapF", "text_ar": "ثَالِثٌ ثَلَاثَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vAlv", "text_ar": "ثالث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being regarded in the former case as though it were a subst.; for you do not mean to convey by it a verbal signification, but only mean that he, or it, is one of the three, or a portion of the three: (Fr, ISk, T, S:) and in like manner you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hiYa vaAlivapu valaAva", "text_ar": "هِىَ ثَالِثَةُ ثَلَاثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She is the third of three"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; but when there is among the females a male, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hiYa vaAlivapu valaAvapK", "text_ar": "هِىَ ثَالِثَةُ ثَلَاثَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", making the masc. to predominate over the fem. (T.) When the two [terms] are different, you may make the former to govern the gen. case or to govern as a verb; saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa raAbiEu", "text_ar": "هُوَ رَابِعُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "valaAvapK", "text_ar": "ثَلَاثَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa raAbiEN valaAvapF", "text_ar": "هُوَ رَابِعٌ ثَلَاثَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaAribu zayodK", "text_ar": "ضَارِبُ زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaAribN zayodFA", "text_ar": "ضَارِبٌ زَيْدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and thus you also say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA vaAlivu", "text_ar": "هٰذَا ثَالِثُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@vonayoni", "text_ar": "ا@ثْنَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA vaAlivN A@vonayoni", "text_ar": "هٰذَا ثَالِثٌ ا@ثْنَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This makes two to be three, with himself,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "itself."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISk, T, * S. [In most copies of the S, for"}, {"kind": "arabic",